Zoom plugin API
===============

1. Setting zoom
1.1 setCentre(CompScreen *s, int x, int y)
1.2 setScale(CompScreen *s, float x, float y)



1. Setting zoom
===============

1.1 setCentre(CompScreen *s, int x, int y)
------------------------------------------
This should define the zoom centre as the x,y coordinates of s.
This should NOT affect the translations. This should only set the centre.

1.2 setScale(CompScreen *s, float x, float y)
---------------------------------------------
This sets the actual zoom. Generally, x should equal y, if it doesn't,
the smallest value should be used. This should ensure that we can see
the entire area we are attempting to fit to. We support diffrent values
for x and y in case we later wish to make it possible to scale in just
one direction. (IE: Break the aspect).


